9 An Act relating to revenue and taxation; amending 68
O.S. 2021, Sections 3113, 3125, 3127, and 3129, as
10 amended by Section 1, Chapter 178, O.S.L. 2023 (68
O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 3129), which relate to
11 procedures for sale of property for unpaid ad valorem
taxes; modifying provisions related to time for
12 redemption of property; prescribing procedures
related to online auctions; providing for effect of
13 certain errors related to information related to tax
sale process; modifying provisions related to method
14 of payment; authorizing online sale process;
prescribing procedures for online sale process; and
15 providing an effective date.
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 3113, is
20 amended to read as follows:
21 Section 3113. The owner of any real estate, or any person
22 having a legal or equitable interest therein, may redeem the same at
23 any time before the execution of a deed of conveyance therefor by
24 the county treasurer start of the resale auction by paying to the
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB1663 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 coun ty treasurer the sum which was originally delinquent including
2 interest at the lawful rate as provided in Section 2913 of this
3 title and such additional costs as may have accrued; provided, that
4 minors or incapacitated or partially incapacitated persons may
5 redeem from taxes any real property belonging to them within one (1)
6 year after the expiration of such disability, with interest and
7 penalty at not more than ten percent (10%) per annum. The term
8 incapacitated as used in this section relates to mental
9 incapacitation only, physical disability is not covered under this
10 term or this section.
11 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 3125, is
12 amended to read as follows:
13 Section 3125. If any real estate shall remain unredeemed for
14 the period provided for in Section 3105 of this title, the county
15 treasurer shall proceed to sell such real estate at resale, which
16 shall be held on the second Monday of June each year in each county
17 or, if conducted through an online auction, shall be started on a
18 date and time set by the county treasurer during normal business
19 hours within the full week of the second Monday of June, or until
20 the sale has concluded pursuant to subsection A of Section 3129 of
21 this title.
22 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 3127, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24
